ce:section.ce:para:
In fact, the system CTe/PEDOT:PSS nanocomposite is still available for the electromagnetic shielding applications until now. Keeping in our mind all the benefits and shortcomings, we engineered the CTe/PEDOT:PSS films as a trail to overcome the above-mentioned problems and achieving the desires. Indeed, a polymeric PEDOT:PSS material has been chosen because of its large electrical conductivities, easy processability, its facile doping tunability, promising bendability, brilliant thermal stability, affordable and its abundance. Also, the main reason behind the selection of PEDOT:PSS is its backbones having a good planarity and its high degree of conjugation which facilitates the interaction between the CTe and PEDOT:PSS (Scheme 1
                     ). Alternatively, Te nanoparticles were chosen thanks to their high stability against environments and surroundings and their well dispersion in aqueous solution. Moreover, the rods morphology in the nano-scale was designed here to increase the ratio of surface-to-volume property which increases the interacted surface areas with EM radiation and therefore improving the EM reflection, absorption and SET values. The CTe nanoparticles have been selected as nano-fillers to improve the electrical conductivity, EM absorption, EM reflection and therefore EM shielding effectiveness. On the other hand, the functional groups (-COO, -COOH, -OH and others) on the Cdots surfaces are the main reasons behind the selection of Cdots to adorn the Te surface which facilitate the interaction between CTe nanoparticles (via functionalized groups) and PEDOT:PSS segments via strong π-π conjugated interfacial interaction and hydrogen H-bonding that can improve the electrical conductivity, EM absorption, EM reflection and EM shielding effectiveness. In this subject, a cut of price, easy fabrication and bendable nano-composite based on (CTe/PEDOT:PSS) shields have been constructed by using the casting method for the electromagnetic shielding application. The microwave synthesized CDots adorned the chemically synthesized Te surface by using the precipitation process and then incorporated into the PEDOT:PSS. The impact of synergetic effect of CDots and Te on the surface morphology, electrical conductivities, dielectric and EM shielding features has been extensively studied according to the matrix (C
                        x
                     Te10-x
                     ), where x is the concentration of Cdots. Actually the in plane // and through plane ⊥ electrical conductivities have been measured and it was found that the higher values of σ// ~ 237.87 ± 5 S/cm and σ⊥ ~ 200.52 ± 4 S/cm were achieved at x = 8 wt% with σ// ~ 1.1σ⊥ owing to the high packing of PEDOT nano-crystallites inside the shield, the increase in carrier mobility, the formation of CTe conductive paths and the synergistic effect of CDots and Te. It was observed, the ε' and ε ' ' values are tuned with the synergistic concentrations inside the films owing to the increment in the concentrations of the free charge carrier's and the interfacial polarizations between the PEDOT:PSS and Te and between Cdots and PEDOT:PSS inside the films. The higher SET of the CTe/PEDOT:PSS composite achieved at x = 8 wt% . A tiny quantity of C8Te2 (x = 8 wt%) nanofillers leads to obtaining a high total shielding SET ~ (63.17 dB) at 8 GHz thanks to the high σ, the synergistic effect of Cdots and Te and the high EM wave absorption features of both Te and Cdots. The SER and SEA varied with x concentration and they were found to be SEA = 45.49 dB and SER = 17.68 dB at 8 GHz for x = 8 wt%. The absorption is the prevailing shielding effectiveness mode in this composite. Finally, this study introduces a new, conductive and an excellent EM wave absorber materials based on PEDOT:SS, Cdots and Te nano-rods. It has been predicted that the CTe/PEDOT:PSS shields have a prospective applications in biological, microwave shielding, electrical and wearable apparatus due to their economic.

