                            values were found to be 180.49 ± 5, 200.59 ± 7, 234.97 ± 7 and 237.87 ± 5 S/cm for 2, 4, 6 and 8 wt%, respectively. As clearly observed, the value of σ

                              //
                            for x = 0 wt% is larger than that for x = 10 wt%. In fact, this result is otherwise the expected results where Te has a high resistivity value which could be expected to decrease the σ

                              //
                            of the film. However the weak interaction (van der waals) between the PEDOT:PSS polymer and Te make the PSS polymers move freely and this in turn facilitates the alignment of PEDOT polymer chains to the film surface producing the anisotropic features. Alternatively, the Cdots are strongly interacted with PEDOT:PSS polymer via π-π interaction and the strong H-bonding which may restrict the polymer chains from moving. As detected, the σ

                              ∥
                            value slightly improved from 180.49 ± 5 S/cm to 237.87 ± 5 S/cm with the increase in (x) from 2 to 8 wt%, and the reason behind this is (i) the synergistic effect of Cdots and Te. (ii) The PEDOT nano-crystals are well- packed inside the matrix. This layer structure of PEDOT is ordered in the in-plane directions create the localization length of carrier larger than molecular spacing and creating high σ

